"v.引出，探出 【英】 v. 引出，探出(to draw forth or bring out) 【记】 e(出)+licit(引导)→ 引导出, 注意不要和illicit( 不合法的)相混 【例】 He elicited the truth at last, by questioning all the boys in the school. v. 引诱出(潜在的某物) = educe; 通过逻辑推理得出 = evoke 【记】e出, licit引一引出 【区】illicit(adj 违法的) 【反】evoke(v 引起)－fail to elicit(不能引起) 【记】e 出 + licit 法律，出离法律→受到引诱造成；可能同源于delicious 美味的，都有诱人之意 【相关】licit(legal, c=g, licence) 合法的，illicit 违法的，educe 导出, 引出，allure 吸引 elicit (v.)  1640s, from Latin elicitus, past participle of elicere ""draw forth,"" from ex- ""out"" (see ex-) + -licere, comb. form of lacere ""to entice, lure, deceive"" (related to laqueus ""noose, snare;"" see lace (n.)). Related: Elicited; eliciting; elicits; elicitation."
